@sayakpan You can use legacy .eslintrc.js until flatcompats issue is resolved
just create this file in root
input boilerplate:
module.exports = {
    extends: ["next/core-web-vitals"],
    parserOptions: {
        ecmaVersion: 2021,
        sourceType: "module",
    },
    rules: {
        // eslint rules you want
    },
};

and start using
npm run lint should not produce any errors anymore

@CvX thanks for finding the cause of the problem.

> As more people move to flat config there might be more issues like this. Perhaps that could be mitigated by a better error message, explaining how to handle config serialization problems?

Any suggestions on what we could add to the error message?
